I helped build the strategic story that connected business ambition, consumer insight, and creative expression into one coherent proposal. That included framing the competitive problem, sharpening the strategic opportunity, defining how the brand should emotionally resonate with Vietnamese urban caregivers, and writing the narrative that carried the client through the deck. I also worked on the language and structure of the presentation so the strategy felt commercially credible, culturally grounded, and creatively differentiated. The resulting proposal articulated not just what C&S should say, but how it should show up over the next **3–5 years** in Vietnam.
